look like, or a tree.

122
00:05:02,091 --> 00:05:05,271
All we wanna do here is show
you how to make these effects.

123
00:05:05,271 --> 00:05:08,471
What you paint is totally up to you.

124
00:05:08,471 --> 00:05:11,291
We just wanna show you how to paint.

125
00:05:11,291 --> 00:05:14,812
Just to get you, just to get you started.

126
00:05:14,812 --> 00:05:19,332
There, now using a big brush
and very firm pressure,

127
00:05:19,333 --> 00:05:21,333
I wanna pull this down.

128
00:05:21,333 --> 00:05:22,813
The only thing we're
worried about right now

129
00:05:22,812 --> 00:05:24,072
is this nice outside edge.

130
00:05:24,072 --> 00:05:26,432
We could care less
what's happening in here.

131
00:05:26,432 --> 00:05:27,733
But once again,

132
00:05:27,733 --> 00:05:30,153
because we have the liquid
white on the canvas,

133
00:05:30,153 --> 00:05:33,853
the color is blending with
that and as you can plainly see

134
00:05:33,853 --> 00:05:35,393
automatically as it goes down

135
00:05:35,392 --> 00:05:38,512
it gets lighter and lighter in value.

136
00:05:38,512 --> 00:05:40,852
And once again, that
will happen automatically

137
00:05:40,853 --> 00:05:42,872
when you have the liquid
white on the canvas.

138
00:05:42,872 --> 00:05:44,552
And it's just an oil base,

139
00:05:44,552 --> 00:05:48,504
white paint that allows
you to do all this.

140
00:05:49,773 --> 00:05:50,894
You can just blend it right on down

141
00:05:50,894 --> 00:05:52,114
and already that mountain looks like

142
00:05:52,113 --> 00:05:54,734
