143
00:05:54,735 --> 00:05:56,574
I tell you what, let's wash the old brush.

144
00:05:56,574 --> 00:05:58,795
That's the fun part of this.

145
00:05:58,795 --> 00:06:00,735
That's the fun part.

146
00:06:00,735 --> 00:06:04,575
Shake off the excess and just,

147
00:06:05,565 --> 00:06:08,357
(chuckling) just beat the devil out of it.

148
00:06:08,358 --> 00:06:10,857
As I say, that's the
part that's the most fun.

149
00:06:11,447 --> 00:06:12,720
There we go.

150
00:06:12,720 --> 00:06:16,080
Let's take some titanium white today.

151
00:06:16,079 --> 00:06:18,979
And we'll reach up here and
I'll get a very small amount

152
00:06:18,980 --> 00:06:20,120
of the dark sienna.

153
00:06:20,120 --> 00:06:22,500
Don't want much, just
a little dark sienna.

154
00:06:23,540 --> 00:06:24,581
A little bit, maybe I'll even

155
00:06:24,581 --> 00:06:26,141
put a touch of the bright red in there.

156
00:06:26,141 --> 00:06:27,122
Oh that's nice.

157
00:06:27,122 --> 00:06:29,141
I just wanna flavor this a little.

158
00:06:29,612 --> 00:06:32,004
Just enough to flavor it a little bit.

159
00:06:32,004 --> 00:06:33,444
Now when you do yours,

160
00:06:33,444 --> 00:06:35,544
you make the determination
how much you want.

161
00:06:35,543 --> 00:06:37,283
Let me wipe the knife here.

162
00:06:37,283 --> 00:06:40,024
And we just wipe our knife
on a clean paper towel.

163
00:06:40,024 --> 00:06:41,925
Then we can cut off our
little roll of paint again,

164
00:06:41,925 --> 00:06:44,606
so it's right on the edge of the knife.

165
00:06:44,607 --> 00:06:49,607
And let's go up in here, no
pressure, no pressure touch.

166
00:06:49,607 --> 00:06:52,810
And let that knife just
float, let it float,

