00:21:37,772 --> 00:21:39,523
He lives in there.

519
00:21:39,523 --> 00:21:42,364
Ole tree now sometimes
they'll hide in there,

520
00:21:42,365 --> 00:21:44,524
you have to sorta force 'em out.

521
00:21:45,946 --> 00:21:47,586
But isn't that a fantastic way

522
00:21:47,586 --> 00:21:51,096
of making some very beautiful evergreens?

523
00:21:52,105 --> 00:21:54,537
Now, shoot, you know me.

524
00:21:55,486 --> 00:21:57,488
I think everybody needs a friend.

525
00:21:57,488 --> 00:21:59,958
So we're gonna give him one right here.

526
00:22:01,188 --> 00:22:02,699
Right there.

527
00:22:04,248 --> 00:22:06,018
There, see, there he comes.

528
00:22:09,748 --> 00:22:11,468
And we're not concerned in this area.

529
00:22:11,468 --> 00:22:15,057
That's all so dark, we'll
separate all that with highlights,

530
00:22:15,938 --> 00:22:17,057
all that with highlights.

531
00:22:17,057 --> 00:22:19,874
Let's take a little bit of that
color we had for our trunk,

532
00:22:19,874 --> 00:22:22,404
and we'll just touch with the knife.

533
00:22:22,404 --> 00:22:25,105
And just once again, we're
not gonna see much of it.

534
00:22:25,105 --> 00:22:26,486
All we wanna do here,

535
00:22:26,486 --> 00:22:29,386
is just show a little,
just here and there.

536
00:22:29,385 --> 00:22:32,555
Just wherever you think it should show.

537
00:22:32,905 --> 00:22:34,495
Like that.

538
00:22:35,505 --> 00:22:38,216
I think I'll was the
ole oval brush out here.

539
00:22:39,546 --> 00:22:42,315
Let's have some fun with
some highlight colors.

540
00:22:43,684 --> 00:22:45,884
Okay now then for
highlights I'm gonna take

541
00:22:45,884 --> 00:22:50,434
a little of that tree color
and mix it with the cad yellow.

542
00:22:51,925 --> 00:22:55,404
And the yellow ochre and a
little of the Indian yellow.

543
00:22:55,404 --> 00:22:57,286
But mix all these colors on the brush

544
00:22:57,286 --> 00:22:59,525
so you have a multitude of
things happening on the brush.

545
00:22:59,525 --> 00:23:01,986
You don't end up with one dead ole color.

546
00:23:02,448 --> 00:23:04,990
Alright, now then think about your light.

547
00:23:04,990 --> 00:23:06,689
It's coming from the right.

548
00:23:06,689 --> 00:23:08,769
Now we can go up in here

549
00:23:08,769 --> 00:23:11,522
and just begin putting in the indication

550
00:23:12,128 --> 00:23:13,471
of some beautiful highlights

551
00:23:13,471 --> 00:23:15,785
that live right here on this tree.

552
00:23:16,442 --> 00:23:17,315
See 'em?

553
00:23:17,315 --> 00:23:18,865
There they are.

554
00:23:19,395 --> 00:23:20,536
There.

555
00:23:20,536 --> 00:23:22,486
Let's just put some in.

556
00:23:24,236 --> 00:23:27,417
But this is where you make
all those old hangy down limbs

557
00:23:27,416 --> 00:23:30,336
and we're going straight in
with the brush, straight in.

558
00:23:30,336 --> 00:23:31,796
And just touching.

559
00:23:31,796 --> 00:23:35,615
Just touching, letting those
top part of the bristles,

560
00:23:35,615 --> 00:23:38,405
just the top part of the bristles touch.

561
00:23:39,976 --> 00:23:41,477
Right there, see there?

562
00:23:41,477 --> 00:23:44,846
Now then, let's go over
on the other side here.

563
00:23:45,278 --> 00:23:47,117
And do the same thing for him.

564
00:23:47,117 --> 00:23:50,469
If we left him out, shoot
he'd probably be angry.

565
00:23:50,919 --> 00:23:52,341
Probably be angry.

566
00:23:52,340 --> 00:23:55,660
We don't want that, we want
happy trees in our paintings.

567
00:23:55,661 --> 00:23:57,539
(chuckles) I get some letters some times,

568
00:23:57,539 --> 00:23:59,941
people say everything
in your world is happy.

569
00:23:59,941 --> 00:24:01,701
And that's true.

570
00:24:01,701 --> 00:24:04,921
We try to keep everything happy in here.

571
00:24:05,911 --> 00:24:08,341
Shoot, if you want bad
stuff, watch the news.

572
00:24:08,340 --> 00:24:12,069
In this world, we only
have pleasant things.

573
00:24:12,540 --> 00:24:13,759
There.

574
00:24:13,759 --> 00:24:15,500
Now then, sometimes it's fun.

575
00:24:15,500 --> 00:24:18,550
I'll just dip this into a
little bit of the liquid clear.

576
00:24:18,901 --> 00:24:21,539
And I want a real thin
color, much lighter,

577
00:24:21,539 --> 00:24:23,340
but I use the clear to thin it.

578
00:24:23,340 --> 00:24:26,400
And then it'll, it's very thin paint now.

579
00:24:26,401 --> 00:24:28,221
You can go back up here and pick out

580
00:24:28,221 --> 00:24:31,240
where you think light would
really zing through here.

581
00:24:31,240 --> 00:24:34,103
And just put on a few sparklers.

582
00:24:34,103 --> 00:24:35,922
Don't over do this.

583
00:24:35,922 --> 00:24:37,305
Don't over do.

584
00:24:37,305 --> 00:24:39,374
'Cause it gets good.

585
00:24:40,565 --> 00:24:41,943
Just here and there.

586
00:24:41,943 --> 00:24:44,527
But that clear thins the paint.

587
00:24:44,527 --> 00:24:45,527
If you've painted with me before

588
00:24:45,527 --> 00:24:46,646
you know our golden rule here

589
00:24:46,646 --> 00:24:49,366
is a thin paint will
stick to a thick paint.

590
00:24:49,366 --> 00:24:52,786
We use very firm paint until
we get to the highlights.

591
00:24:53,965 --> 00:24:55,948
And maybe just a few over in here,

592
00:24:55,949 --> 00:24:58,318
I don't want too many on this tree.

593
00:24:59,248 --> 00:25:01,439
Just a few, there.

594
00:25:03,250 --> 00:25:04,900
Alright, we're alright there.

595
00:25:05,469 --> 00:25:06,769
Let's have some fun.

596
00:25:06,769 --> 00:25:08,348
Now we have a transparent color here.

597
00:25:08,348 --> 00:25:11,948
This was sap green and a
little bit of Van Dyke brown,

598
00:25:11,949 --> 00:25:12,850
just to dull it.

599
00:25:12,849 --> 00:25:16,690
I'm gonna take pure
white, just titanium white

600
00:25:16,691 --> 00:25:17,990
on the two inch brush.

601
00:25:17,990 --> 00:25:19,671
You have to make a big decision,

602
00:25:19,671 --> 00:25:21,331
where is your water?

603
00:25:21,330 --> 00:25:22,910
I want some water in here.

604
00:25:22,911 --> 00:25:25,132
Touch this and pull it straight down.

605
00:25:25,132 --> 00:25:27,464
It's important that it
comes straight down.

606
00:25:28,592 --> 00:25:30,314
Then that sap green and Van Dyke brown,

607
00:25:30,314 --> 00:25:33,413
they'll make some
beautiful, beautiful colors.

608
00:25:34,233 --> 00:25:36,715
And it's fun to prepare this
canvas when nobody's looking

609
00:25:36,715 --> 00:25:38,115
and when you do this,

610
00:25:38,115 --> 00:25:39,855
especially if you're painting for someone,

611
00:25:39,855 --> 00:25:41,195
they think it's magic.

612
00:25:41,195 --> 00:25:42,877
Now we go straight across.

613
00:25:42,877 --> 00:25:45,797
And that'll create the illusion of water.

614
00:25:45,797 --> 00:25:47,217
That easy.

615
00:25:47,217 --> 00:25:50,397
Now take a one inch brush, put
a little liquid white on it

616
00:25:50,396 --> 00:25:52,788
and go right through some of that color.

617
00:25:53,278 --> 00:25:55,387
Just a nice green color.

618
00:25:55,737 --> 00:25:57,757
And let's back in here, put the indication

619
00:25:57,757 --> 00:26:00,837
of just a happy little bush
or two that lives right here,

620
00:26:00,837 --> 00:26:02,748
right on the edge of the water.

621
00:26:03,438 --> 00:26:05,228
Something like that.

622
00:26:06,077 --> 00:26:09,261
Little Van Dyke brown, a little
dark sienna mixed together.

623
00:26:09,261 --> 00:26:13,961
And we can put the indication
of some land back in there.

624
00:26:13,961 --> 00:26:15,063
See there?

625
00:26:15,063 --> 00:26:16,422
That easy.

626
00:26:16,422 --> 00:26:17,783
A little bit of brown and white,

627
00:26:17,782 --> 00:26:19,582
put a little highlight on it.

628
00:26:19,583 --> 00:26:21,243
Shoot, we're in business.

629
00:26:21,242 --> 00:26:22,123
A little bit more of that color.

630
00:26:22,123 --> 00:26:26,092
Maybe there's a shoo, looky there.

631
00:26:26,863 --> 00:26:29,582
Little bank lives out here too, see,

632
00:26:29,582 --> 00:26:32,423
just sorta let that go,
barely, barely touching though.

633
00:26:33,692 --> 00:26:35,065
And a little bit on the other side.

634
00:26:35,065 --> 00:26:37,713
See, we can put another bank over here.

635
00:26:38,765 --> 00:26:40,905
In your world, you make these decisions,

636
00:26:40,904 --> 00:26:43,335
decide where all these little things live.

637
00:26:44,185 --> 00:26:48,285
Take a little touch of the
liquid white on the knife.

638
00:26:48,286 --> 00:26:50,765
And we'll just cut in a little water line.

639
00:26:50,765 --> 00:26:54,206
And this separates, just separates.

640
00:26:54,205 --> 00:26:56,997
It's just straight liquid white.

641
00:26:58,128 --> 00:26:59,987
A few little ripples here and there.

642
00:26:59,988 --> 00:27:02,357
Shoot we 'bout have a finished painting.

643
00:27:04,407 --> 00:27:08,207
I think that, I think
we'll call that one done.

644
00:27:08,208 --> 00:27:10,948
But this is a good example of
how easy this technique is.

645
00:27:10,948 --> 00:27:12,449
So I look forward to seeing
you in the next show.

646
00:27:12,449 --> 00:27:16,188
And until then, happy
painting, God bless my friend.

